Project name :- Moduler and packager

Multi Utility Toolkit is a Python menu-driven application that demonstrates the use of different Python modules and packages. 
This project combines multiple utilities such as date and time operations, mathematical calculations, random data generation, UUID generation, and file handling in a single application.

--> Features:-

1.  Date and Time Operations
- Display current date and time
- Find difference between two dates
- Format date and time
- Stopwatch functionality
- Countdown timer

2. Mathematical Operations
- Calculate factorial
- Calculate compound interest
- Perform trigonometric calculations
- Calculate area of a circle

3. Random Data Generation
- Generate random numbers
- Generate random lists
- Generate random passwords
- Generate OTP numbers

4. UUID Generation
- Generate unique identifiers using UUID module

5. File Operations
- Create a file
- Write data into a file
- Read file contents
- Append data to an existing file

6. Module Exploration
- Display attributes and methods of Python modules using dir() function

--> Concepts Covered:-
- Functions
- Modules and Packages
- Menu Driven Programming
- File Handling
- Conditional Statements
- Loops
- Exception-free User Interaction
- dir() Function
__name__ == "__main__" Usage

--> Sample Main Menu:-
1. Datetime and Time Operations
2. Mathematical Operations
3. Random Data Generation
4. Generate UUID
5. File Operations
6. Explore Module Attributes
7. Exit

--> Conclusion:-
The Multi Utility Toolkit project provides practical experience with Python modules and packages by integrating multiple utilities into a
 single application. It improves understanding of modular programming, code reusability, and real-world application development.

